SensePrefs - Class in nl.sense_os.service.constants
Contains all preference keys for the SharedPreferences that are used by the Sense library.

Nota bene: there are three separate preference files: SensePrefs.MAIN_PREFS, containing the settings for the sensors and sample and sync rates; SensePrefs.AUTH_PREFS, containing all user-related stuff like login, session, cached sensor IDs; SensePrefs.STATUS_PREFS, containing settings about which sensors are activated. To access the settings, you should not uses the default SharedPreference, but use the names of the right preference file instead:

SenseService - Class in nl.sense_os.service
Main Sense service class.

Activities can bind to this service and call functions to: log in; register; start sensing; start/stop individual sensor modules; set and get properties; When the #toggleMain(boolean) method is called to start the sensing, the service starts itself and registers itself as a foreground service so it does not get easily killed by Android.
